snippet: King Abdullah II moved to block a 10 percent increase in fuel prices after protesters took to the streets over the weekend, raising the specter of renewed social unrest in the cash-poor kingdom.
abstract: King Abdullah II of Jordan moves to block a 10 percent increase in gasoline and diesel fuel prices after protesters take to the streets, raising the specter of renewed social unrest in the cash-poor kingdom.

byline.original: By RANYA KADRI and ISABEL KERSHNER
byline.contributor: Ranya Kadri reported from Amman, and Isabel Kershner from Jerusalem.

lead_paragraph: King Abdullah II moved to block a 10 percent increase in fuel prices after protesters took to the streets over the weekend, raising the specter of renewed social unrest in the cash-poor kingdom.

headline.seo: Jordan’s King Abdullah Cancels Fuel Price Rise in Face of Protest
